<br>
This started a long long time ago, in a land far far away.... Crushbone actually. When I was level 7.<br>
<br>
I was new to everquest, and while messing about at the crushbone entrance two people I had never met before came and helped me out. They were Rintro and Saralena from Shanara's Legacy. After demonstrating my skills at running away screaming like a lil girl totally at random, much to their amusement, they decided to invite me into their guild. Rintro was only level 30 then, and sara was level 20.<br>
<br>
Over a long period of time I made many friends in the guild, and by the time I was level 20 I had earned the title of the Mad Mage, due to totally erratic behavior, bad puns, and generally not taking anything TOO seriously.<br>
<br>
About that time I discovered the Gfey trader's market.<br>
<br>
I had managed to scrounge up about 300pp, and rintro loaned me 700 more. With that I began trading. I bought items cheaply, sold them for a little more, and started earning money. Eventually by doing this I earned quite a lot of money and took on some business partners.<br>
<br>
Around then rintro made me an officer in Shanara's and I began recruiting.<br>
<br>
Everyone around my level I asked to join. Taking in players of a higher level when I could, and using the contacts I made while trading to recruit even more heavily.<br>
<br>
I started leading guild meetings when Rintro neglected to show up, and began to take a more active role in SL. Eventually, by unanamious vote becoming the second in command of the guild.<br>
<br>
I used the new equipment I had purchaced to level as quickly as I could, but I was still far behind my peers, as ironically, the time I had spent trading they had spent leveling. And while I still had extremely good equipment for my level, I was falling behind and they were not.<br>
<br>
Time passed and eventually I had about all the equipment I needed. So I used the remaining items I had left to start a guild bank. A friend of mine took up smithing and put in some tarnished weapons, and others collected the 4 paw scrolls from SK needed for the mele glove quest.<br>
<br>
Around this time, due to a trading bug I lost 8 bags of equipment. Basically, my character saved while I had a trade window up, and then I went linkdead. EQ restored the last character save... which was the one with me having an empty inventory due to having all my stuff in trade windows. I lost about 30k worth of inventory.<br>
<br>
Vedan, the server GM at the time, kindly went through and restored all the items I had lost, one at a time. Due to me being a merchant this happened again. and again. and again.<br>
<br>
The guild bank was fairly safe during this, people were donating some decent items and PP. All of which promptly left the bank and went to those who needed it.<br>
<br>
All that remained were the things no one wanted, the 4 paw scrolls, and the tarnished weapons.<br>
<br>
Now, a bit of background on Shanara's legacy. The guild was created late 2000 by someone named Perc in tribute to his wife, in game and out, Alora Shanara. He held the guild for about a week, before retiring and passing it on to someone else. They lasted nearly a month before passing it on to Gokusan, the leader at the time I had joined.<br>
<br>
Goku later went into temporary retirement and handed the guild over to Rintro.<br>
<br>
At some point Saralena, a good friend and calming influence on rintro, left. And rintro became a bit more... Erratic.<br>
<br>
Now, around November of last year, I ran into Perc while in gfey. And with much encouragement, invited him back into the guild.<br>
<br>
A few weeks later, Rintro said he was planning on leaving the guild and turning over leadership to perc, because perc had asked for it. He confided in me that he felt that SL wasn't going anywhere. And he was planning on merging about 6 guilds together to create a guild called Forbidden Alliance, with the help of several of his friends. Whereupon we would allow those members of SL who still wanted rintro's leadership to join.<br>
<br>
And so I moved from being Rintro's second in command, to being perc's. That night was also the night I invited velasaris into the guild.<br>
<br>
And then, that evening, my computer blew up. Literally.<br>
<br>
One of my many vices is a fierce addiction to nicotine, and I had been smoking around my computer for several months. The smoke had condensed on the intake fan and created tar. The tar collected dust until the intake fan just stopped. My power supply overheated and blew up. Fortunately that was the only part of the computer to be damaged.<br>
<br>
Around that time Dragon Warrior 7 was released. And so I took my time repairing it, enjoying my newest toy. When I did finally get my computer fixed and logged back in, I found the guild in ruins. From having well over 100 members of various levels, we were down to about 20, give or take. And Perc was no longer leading the guild, but Alora was.<br>
<br>
In my absence, perc had once again decided to give up SL, but rather than give it back to rintro, he gave it to his wife while he moved to another server. I don't need to tell you all how... vocal rintro can be. Needless to say they were not pleased with this new opposition.<br>
<br>
When I returned, no one I knew was there, save for a few people I remembered inviting. All my friends had left. Either joining other guilds, or switching servers. There are some I haven't found yet, tho I continue to look whenever I log on.<br>
<br>
At this time, Rintro wasn't on. At all that I could see. I wanted to talk with him before I made my decision. Stay with alora, or help Rintro found the Forbidden Alliance as we had planned.<br>
<br>
So I waited, and bided my time by continuing to trade in gfey. At this point I stopped donating items into the bank, as no one else was, and no one who had donated anything remained in the guild. The bank I had created was for a guild that no longer existed. And yet it remained. With it's newbie items that no one wanted, the 4 paw scrolls, and the tarnished weapons.<br>
<br>
I eventually figured that no one was going to want it, so I decided to sell it to vendors and give it out to random newbies. However I put it off and forgot about this decision, putting the bank alt away and focusing on making money with Faelawen.<br>
<br>
It was then that I once again found Rintro.<br>
<br>
He informed me that yes, he was planning on forming a new guild, called Defiant Heroes.<br>
<br>
It's important that you all understand something. Shanara's under rintro wasn't uber. There were only a few members over lvl 30. But we had fun, and nothing but. We woud play games with the guild message of the day, tell jokes in guildchat, just generally screw around. Because it didn't matter. We weren't uber, and we didn't care to be.<br>
<br>
When Perc and Alora took charge that all vanished. I don't blame them. What they tried to do was put order into an inherently disorderly system. And SL wasn't ready for that.<br>
<br>
Around the time Rintro was telling me of DH, I experienced another massive item loss. my 5th so far. I petitioned and sent yet another e-mail to vedan, planning on getting back to him when I could locate him online.<br>
<br>
At the next guild meeting I told those who I knew would miss the old days that Rintro was forming a new guild, one that would hopefully mirror the early days of SL. Alora was not pleased with this, and I was not pleased with the way she gained power, or the regimented systems she was trying to introduce.<br>
<br>
In retrospect, after having lead this guild for nearly a year, she was right. In part. We just weren't ready for it yet. She tried to move us too far, too fast and with not enough people.<br>
<br>
It was then that Alora began to ask questions about the guild bank. Being the flake that I am I was under the impression that I had already gotten rid of the dregs that remained in there, and told her not to concern herself with it, as there was nothing of any value in there.<br>
<br>
Still upset at me for attempting to move what remained of the backbone of SL to the new guild rintro was creating, she accused me of stealing the items and selling them for my own profit, claiming that the 50k I managed to make in one day was entirely due to the items I had stold from the guild bank. How she reached the conclusion that a 1-35ish guild managed to come up with 50k in donations in the 3 or so months that the guild bank had existed for, remains a mystery to me. (The way I did it was buying a nocvigant blade for about 50pp and selling it about an hour later for 15k, rinse, repeat.)<br>
<br>
Furious at the accusation, I /guildremoved myself and moved on.<br>
<br>
Now, shortly thereafter I sought out vedan to once again create, item by item, what I had lost. He was getting rather sick of it so rather than spend about 2 hours recreating the lot of it, he overwrote my character with a save from about 2 days previous, then went through the trades I had made in the interim.<br>
<br>
It was after that that I discovered that the older character save he had used was still a member and officer of shanara's legacy.<br>
<br>
I didn't discover this until velasarius tactfully pointed it out by telling me to &quot;Get the @#%$ out of our guild.&quot; Whereupon I told him about the character overwrite and told him not to worry, that I'd be /guildremoving a second time shortly.<br>
<br>
He did not accept my explaination then and obviously still doesn't. So, just to run over it one last time... The reason you couldn't boot me vel was because I was an officer. Rintro couldn't have reinvited me with an alt because no one but the guild leader, Alora, can promote someone to officer status. So either I hacked into alora's account, promptly dashed out to buy a new computer and a second copy of EQ, logged on to fae and promoted myself, then rushed out and sold it again. Or vedan overwrote my character with an older backup.<br>
<br>
Now, what proceeded to transpire was this. Not accepting my explaination, I was repeatedly insulted with extreme vulgarity, called a hacker, a liar and a thief, and grilled on which officer invited me and promoted me to officer status. Prob #1 being stated above, and prob #2 being that the only officers logged on when I mysteriously reappeared were the ones that wanted my head on a stick.<br>
<br>
Rather than just /guildremove myself again, I attempted to defend myself and my actions, which was probably a mistake, as there's not a lot you can say to the lynch mob when they come knocking. However some of the cooler heads that evening listened and joined myself and rintro in DH.<br>
<br>
Ahh DH. If you want to know why vel hates myself, rintro, and DH with such a passion Oumlager, there it is. It was a guild split. And a bad one. Usually these things are kept private. And I know you've all been through your share. However, since vel seems so keen to dredge what happened a year ago into all this, there it is in it's entirety.<br>
<br>
After the founding of DH it went well. for a while. and then rintro became even more erratic. He began to become literally intelligible with the things he was saying in game, and began doing many things that made little or no sense. Fiercely fighting against even the simplest issues. This all culminated in the incident with the kromrif military leggings between Rintro and you, Oumlager.<br>
<br>
At that point I told him that it might be wise if he were to give control of the guild to me, until such a time as he got his behavior back under control. He complied, and transfered ownership of DH to me. <br>
<br>
Now, we're not about &quot;No one @#%$ with us&quot; or being &quot;leet&quot;. What we are about now is attempting to help others in any way we can, and letting our friendship and the unity of the guild carry us into the higher level game. We are no longer the lvl 30 people hanging out attempting to raid paw and such. We are now almost entirely comprised of well trained, devoted members over level 45 and we are recruiting more by the day.<br>
<br>
You say there's a stain on this guild? There's only like 4 people aside from myself out of the origional 40 odd folks I managed to round up out of the old shanaras. They're people who've proven they're loyalty and devotion to helping others time and time again. We are not the guild you think you know. Rintro no longer has any contact or affiliation with DH and frankly, I think we're all a lot better off that way. And if you have a problem with me personally vel, because of what happened that night when you were alora's second in command and I stold your thunder, get over it. It was nearly a full year ago. I'd like to think that at least a few of us have matured since then.<br>
<br>
This was a painful time for all involved, and it's not something that's fun to talk about. But it needed to be said.<br>
<br>
We are not perfect, and we do have flaws. But the flaws we have are not related to our members. There is no such thing as a perfect system. The best we can hope for is to get close.<br>
<br>
Whatever grudge you harbor against me vel, I am sorry for it. And in the future I hope to prove your opinions of me and my guild wrong. <br>
<br>
<br>
Until then,<br>
<br>
Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar. Leader of the Defiant Heroes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uryverthorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ryverthorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/14/02 7:01:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> a few opinions from a humble mage </span><hr size=1> I was there during the time that a lot of this happened as well.  I was a member of SL and one of the founding members of DH.  I remember when I found out that Alora had become the leader of SL and that Rintro and Faelawen were going to start another guild I wanted to be first in line to sign up.  I did not then, and still do not hold anything against Alora or SL...  I saw it as wanting to support people that I had grown to know and love through my interactions with them, people that had become my friends.   I recall that Faelawen had been having a lot of problems (as he stated above) with items disappearing and how frustrated he was getting having to contact gms every other day to have the problem fixed.  One thing that I think bothered me a great deal during this time was the fact that Alora and certain members of SL became quite angry when Fae and Rintro made the announcement that DH was going to be formed.  Fae and Rintro had made the announcement in guild chat, and were promptly told not to recruit within the guild.  In my humble opinion, there was no reason why they should not have made the announcement in guild chat.  It gave people a chance to know what was going on and allowed them the choice of staying with SL or following Rintro and Faelawen.  For some reason Alora and some of the officers of SL were threatened